june   feb    dec   december   feb    jun   june   feb    dec   december   feb    jun   june   feb    dec   december   feb    jun   june   feb   corporate governance corporate governance statement board charters board of directors charter audit risk  compliance committee charter nomination  remuneration committee charter policies directors’ code of conduct director independence policy continuous disclosure policy communications policy risk management policy securities trading policy diversity policy constitution piml business rules of conduct  personal investing rules board and secretary board secretary and committees membership michael cole becon mecon ffin independent nonexecutive director chairman and member of the audit risk  compliance committee and nomination  remuneration committee since  april  mr cole has over  years of experience in the investment banking and the funds management industry  he was an executive director  executive vice president at bankers trust australia limited for over  years  mr cole is chairman of ironbark capital limited and imb limited  mr cole is the chairman and director of challenger listed investments limited anne loveridge ba hons fca australia fca england and wales gaicd independent nonexecutive director chair of the audit risk  compliance committee since  february  and member of the nomination  remuneration committee ms loveridge is currently a nonexecutive director for the national australia bank nab group and has over  years of experience as a former partner in the financial services assurance practice at pricewaterhousecoopers pwc where she worked with a range of clients in banking property private equity and wealth management sectors providing advice on financial and regulatory reporting risk management controls and compliance frameworks stephen menzies becon llb llm independent nonexecutive director member of the audit risk  compliance committee and chair of the nomination  remuneration committee since  june  mr menzies is currently a director of century australia investments limited and chairman of the centre for quantum computation  communication technology mr menzies retired as a partner at ashurst law firm last year and until his retirement was consistently ranked as one of australias leading corporate lawyers as head of china practice for ashurst he oversaw the shanghai and beijing offices of that firm as a senior lawyer he managed legal work of significant projects in capital markets and mergers including some of the largest transactions in australia previously mr menzies was national director for enforcement at the australian securities commission and has a long history in the funds management sector kerr neilson bcom asip managing director since  july  mr neilson was appointed as managing director upon incorporation of platinum investment management limited  prior to platinum mr neilson was an executive vice president at bankers trust australia limited previously he worked in both the uk and south africa in stockbroking andrew clifford bcom hons director and chief investment officer since  may  mr clifford joined platinum as a cofounding member in  in the capacity of deputy chief investment officer and is a director of platinum investment management limited   previously he was a vice president of bankers trust australia limited covering asian equities and managing the bt select market trust  pacific basin fund  mr clifford is coportfolio manager for the platinum international fund elizabeth norman ba grad dip fp director since  may  ms norman joined platinum in february  in the role of investor services and communications manager  previously she worked at bankers trust australia limited in product development and within the retail funds management team  ms normans role as director of investor services and communications reflects the widening of platinums client base and the companys greater commitment to supporting retail and institutional clients with dedicated investment specialists andrew stannard bmgt hons grad dip afi cadirector since  august  mr stannard joined platinum from alliancebernstein where he held the position of chief financial officer for the asiapacific region mr stannard has  years of finance experience with expertise in audit financial control operations funds management financial services regulation and corporate governance he is a chartered accountant joanne jefferies bcommllbcompany secretary since october  ms jefferies joined platinum from bnp paribas securities services where she held the positions of regional head of legal for asia pacific and company secretary ms jefferies has over  years of legal experience with expertise in funds management financial services regulation and corporate governance ms jefferies holds a bachelor of laws and a bachelor of commerce degree     corporate responsibility and sustainability building a sustainable business  was a milestone year – platinum celebrated its th anniversary and its funds under management fum exceeded a billion from a startingpoint of a team of four investment professionals and a handful of support staff platinum has built a strong brand name and a reputation that is the envy of the financial services industry  this reputation has been achieved by staying true to platinum’s key objective – delivering superior returns over time and communicating the intricacies of global investing and providing investors with steady longterm performance the business of platinum is to manage clients’ money  it charges clients a fee for doing so and these fees are platinum’s chief source of revenue  we at platinum have a simple core belief  if platinum responsibly and successfully looks after investors’ money its business should prosper  a failure to understand and commit to this priority will not result in an enduring wealth management business marketing commissions and other devices notwithstanding being a responsible money manager history of strong performance our history has been punctuated with recurrent market challenges – the asian monetary crisis of  the tech bubble of  and the more recent global financial crisis of   in spite of these challenges we have seized the many opportunities presented by the market and have over the longterm typically outperformed the benchmark msci index by a significant margin  as at  may  the flagship platinum international fund had achieved an average compound annual return of  since its inception in  compared to  for the msci all country world net index  indeed the majority of our platinum trust funds have performed strongly over the longterm delivering superior returns to our investors click here for more information on the performance of all publicly available platinum funds investment process how did we achieve these strong returns  platinum is wellknown for its distinctive stock selection methodology which seeks out a broad range of investments where the market has for transient reasons mispriced their business  to do this platinum employs a team of highly skilled specialist analysts who take a global perspective and apply screening and intensive research to isolate real as opposed to imagined issues in applying platinum’s thematic contrarian investment method we build each portfolio from individual stock selections rather than from any predetermined asset allocation at times whole sectors or industries may be misunderstood and this can give rise to several investments in that and related areas we pay no heed to the weightings of any benchmark such as the msci index   investment risks are actively monitored and managed through appropriate measures such as the use of derivatives and currency hedging where permitted under the fund’s mandate a more detailed description of our investment process can be found here and click here for further information on platinum’s risk management strategies better engagement with investors in addition to the core principle of striving for superior longterm performance in global equity investments platinum’s business has been founded on the following precepts no upfront fees no exit fees no trailing commissions to financial intermediaries or advisers no soft dollar benefits paid to or received from financial advisers or advisory firms forward pricing no “market timing” or “late trading” of unit trust products we support financial advisers with quality presentations from the investment team we give biennial investor presentations for those investing directly with us we provide clear and engaging quarterly investor reports we provide consistent high service standards to clients and advisers all of these principles were adopted with the single aim of better servicing our clients and none of which has altered over the  years of platinum’s growth ethical conduct the ethical standards of the financial services industry have been facing increasing scrutiny worldwide since the global financial crisis  platinum has always held the highest standards of integrity and honesty and has put in place robust policies aiming to prevent unethical conduct such as fraud bribery and insider trading  given the nature of platinum’s business we are particularly mindful of the risks of insider trading and personal dealing  platinum has therefore implemented appropriate systems of ongoing monitoring and regular training to ensure compliance by all staff members with our business rules of conduct and trading policy ethical investment platinum regards the subject of ethical investing as highly complex and points to the contradictions and conflicts that are an essential element of the capitalist system  we have no way of individually assessing the beliefs and values of our investors or the companies in which we invest cognisant of the diversity of views on these subjects platinum decided at this stage not to adopt any formalised ethical investment policy in selecting retaining and realising investments  however that is not to say that ethical considerations such as environmental responsibility and labour standards do not play a part in our investment process  our investment analysts routinely take such factors into consideration when assessing the overall quality and sustainability of an investment prospect it has been our experience that when our values of fair play and ethics are upheld by the company under scrutiny it tends to lead to fewer disappointments as an investment  to adopt a more formal set of ethical investment criteria would require platinum to develop a template of ethical values that hopefully satisfies the majority of unit holders on matters including labour standards environmental impact social intercourse political system governance behaviour and standards national institutions and so on  in our view it is not possible to create such a template without unduly imposing a set of values on all investors regardless of whether they share these values workplace diversity and flexibility in a serviceoriented business like platinum our people are our greatest asset  that is why we focus equally on attracting the best talent and providing an inclusive and supportive work environment for our staff platinum actively promotes a culture of equal opportunity and has the principles of meritocracy fairness equality and contribution to commercial success at all levels within the company  we value the blend of skills perspectives styles and attitudes available to the company through a diverse workforce and recognise that such diversity has contributed to our business success  for example our investment research team includes not only economists and finance experts but also scientists and engineers  you can find more information about our investment team here in this context workplace diversity includes gender age ethnicity cultural background and more  to promote workplace diversity our board has adopted a diversity policy in addition to a workplace antidiscrimination  antiharassment policy  the diversity policy includes a set of clear objectives as part of our corporate governance practice  these include to provide flexibility to staff members  in this context workplace flexibility involves developing people management strategies that accommodate differences in background perspectives and family responsibilities of staff to include in the recruitment process for vacant positions a diversified group including gender diversity of candidates  this further extends to the interview process for vacant positions on platinum’s board of directors to provide training opportunities with the aim of bringing through the underlying potential of staff established a diversity committee comprising representatives from each business area  the diversity committee will meet periodically and will monitor progress on boardrecommended diversity strategies and make recommendations to the board for further diversity opportunities the following statistics current as of  may  demonstrate platinum’s ongoing endeavours to promote diversity and flexible work arrangements  this has allowed platinum to exceed the country’s average in many aspects for example the representation of women on the board and in senior executive positions women employed on a parttime basis and the percentage of workforce made up of people born outside australia   diversity criteria platinum  australia  women on the board   of   women in senior executive positions   of   women in the workforce   of   women in line roles   of   women employed on a parttime basis   of   workforce over  years of age   of   workforce made up of people born outside australia   of   workforce made up of people with tertiary qualifications   of   workforce made up of people identified as aboriginal or torres strait islander people   of   platinum’s efforts to create an inclusive and supportive work culture have resulted in excellent retention rates  for example the average investment management industry experience of our fund managers was  years as at  may  